casebody.data:
Laura Lynn SUTLIEF, Respondent,
v.
Martin Edward SUTLIEF, Appellant. WD 81126 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Filed: August 28, 2018 Martin E. Sutlief, Gladstone, Appellant pro se. Andrea P. Bolstad, Liberty for respondent. Before Division Two: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, Lisa White Hardwick and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judges

ORDER

Per Curiam

Martin Sutlief appeals from the judgment dissolving his marriage to Laura Sutlief. He contends the circuit court's judgment was not final because the court failed to dispose of all of the marital property. Upon review of the briefs and the record, we find no error and affirm the judgment. We have provided the parties with a Memorandum explaining the reasons for our decision, because a published opinion would have no precedential value.

AFFIRMED. Rule 84.16(b).
